jwks.description:
The JWKS object contains the set of parameters that are read by an OIDC
compliant server to validate a JWT issued by an OIDC provider.

alg.description:
Alg defines the algorithm used for signing as per the JWKS specification (RFC
7518 section 7).

curve.description:
Curve is the curve type used for signing. Valid only when signing method is EC
(RFC 7518 section 6).

e.description:
E is the exponent value of an RSA public key. Valid only when the signing
method is RSA (RFC 7518 section 6).

kid.description: kid is the key ID as per the JWKS specification.

kty.description: kty defines the key type as per the JWKS specification.

n.description:
N is the modulos value of an RSA public key. Valid only when the signing
method is RSA (RFC 7518 section 6).

use.description: Use defines the use of the signing key as per the JWKS specification.

x.description:
X is the X value of the public key. Valid only when signing method is EC (RFC
7518 section 6).

y.description:
Y is the Y value of the public key. Valid only when signing method is EC (RFC
7518 section 6).
